<tr><td bgcolor="#3F403F" width="98%" class="cheader"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></td><td bgcolor="3F403F" valign="top" align="right" width="22"><img src="/swtcg/gfx/theme1/topcorner.gif" width="23" height="22" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0" align="right"></td></tr>
<tr><td width="98%" colspan=2><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" class="cbody">
<tr><td><font class="h1font"> Droids:  The Swarm<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/swtcg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/swtcg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/swtcg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/swtcg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.43)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/swtcg/main/mpage.php?member=8828'>Joseph "Jorien Fett" Orion</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/swtcg/main/mpage.php?member=8828&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> May 20, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> I&#39;ve played some Dark Side decks that focused on the Character and Space arenas, but get totally wiped out in the Ground battle.  Here&#39;s a quick way to balance it out and make your deck a little tougher using those pesky droids.  <br>
<br>
SPACE ARENA<br>
<br>
In the space arena, there is one thing you MUST get out here and that is the Droid Control Ship.  It&#39;s an expensive unit at 9 but a 9/9 unit that gives each droid in all arenas +10 speed is amazing.  Now it doesn&#39;t say &quot;battle droid&quot; or &quot;destroyer droid&quot;  It&#39;s just DROID.  It&#39;s imperative that you get as many of these suckers out in the space as possible.  But don&#39;t worry if you can only get one out.  One is better than none.  Take The Initiative is a wonderful card to toss in those Geonosian and Droid Starfighters after they get toasted, to protect the droid control ship.  Cards like Starship Refit will heal your Control Ship ASAP.  If that control ship goes down, ALL droids get a universal hit.<br>
<br>
GROUND ARENA<br>
Now of course you want fast units that hit hard.  Destroyer Droid Squad are the only ones that are the bang for the buck...or ARE they?  Look at those Battle Droid Squads...so slow but with the control ship, they&#39;re now at 20 speed.  Still not impressed?  Definitely put some Luxury Speeders in the Ground arena as well and now your droids are +10 more for each Speeder.  To poli all of, Dark Speeds work wonders.  They&#39;re free, and they give a unit +30 speed!  The big boys from the Commerce Guild also get built up.  Imagine being able to ION Cannon or Attack Ground forces before the AT-TE walkers!  You can do it if you&#39;ve got the right units out there.<br>
<br>
CHARACTER ARENA<br>
Everyone falls into the same trap by putting a million Jangos/Tyranus&#39; in the Character Arena.  Super Battle Droids are going to be +10 speed and +1 power if you run a droid deck.  It&#39;s a given.  Now using the Control Ship as well?  Now he&#39;s +20 speed.  which turns an already intimidating 40-4/4 into a 60-5/4 monster!  And then of course there are the Destroyer droids.  These guys have Shields plus they also get +20 speed or +2 power at the beginning of each turn.  Being already 40 speed, the droid ship will most likely be out there, thus making it a 50-5-4 destroyer.  From there it&#39;s your choice, make him 70-5-4, or 50-7-4.  This can compare to your main baddies!<br>
<br>
The purpose of using droids is to have them feed off of each other to become meaner, stronger, faster.  In both the Character and Space, the main goal is to swarm the enemy with cheap costing units, using Hatch A Clone and Take The Initiative to get your units back.  Dark Rendevouz is an excellent card for 4 build points.  Your opponent will lose 7 force and that should leave them wide open to attacks, no dodging everything that comes at them.  <br>
<br>
So don&#39;t be afraid to use Droids.  They&#39;re excellent for the cost and all feed off of each other for mutual benefit.  Don&#39;t forget to throw Geonosian Squads in there for ground as well (critical hit 3 is just insane for a 4-build unit!)  You should have a swarm of droids winning the game for you in no time. <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/swtcg/articles/articles.php?id=3698&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/swtcg/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></td></tr></table>
